				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard Twink Guide<a name="75861"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 26 05 9:08 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>dunno gear these days, I would just go to the bazaar on your server and shop around for a couple weeks to see what's available and learn what good prices are.  I filter by HP when I do that, because I'm a HP fan, but you could also choose to filter by Charisma or AC or whatever  (HP STA and AC will serve you best in my opinion until at least the 50s)
<br />

<br />
&quot;Would I be able to do the OT Hammer quest with Tribunal faction? &quot;
<br />

<br />
Not positive, but I could do it very easily as an agnostic wood elf - get the DE mask and fire up the faction song and you're gtg, just don't hunt anywhere that hurts your OT faction first.
<br />

<br />
&quot;What instruments are the best combo for soloing up to the 50s? 
<br />

<br />
Just look for the highest mod you can find in the bazaar.  (The mods show on the instrument's item description; higher is better.) The two I would prioritize are lute (heals) and drum (chants and runspeed). A good lute combined with the fungi will usually let you heal up fast. 
<br />

<br />
&quot;When do I need to look at FT items and what's a good amount to have by 60ish?&quot;
<br />

<br />
(Unless there's a new song I don't know about,) FT serves no purpose whatsoever until you get the 39 charm, which is the first song to use mana.   FT5 lets me charm as much as I want without running OOM.  Once you get Fading Memories (AA that you won't be able to buy till 63),  you will want as much as possible (and you will start wanting a bigger mana pool too), since that uses a big chunk of mana per use. 
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
